comments.body:
@rhatdan @baude so this _was_ flaking heavily last week, but something happened around/before 5646f13178b6bae13c359c69610c43af2afee0e1 (ironic, but no humor intended).  My best guess is the un-flake was probably related to bfc544f7e8051057a4e3e2a0825f611aebd7400b - since it was merged around the same time.

So unfortunately now, healthcheck does not appear to be flaking anymore.  ***However*** I think this _might_ be an excellent topic for a new healthcheck test:  Confirm healthcheck behaves correctly when the container exits immediately (IIRC, this was related to the cause being investigated in this PR?).

If you agree, I would be in favor of closing this PR but opening an issue for a new test.  I would open the issue myself, but I don't have the technical background to adequately describe/suggest how this should be tested.  OTOH, given a sufficient general description in the issue, I could take a stab at writing the test :smile:
